result.execSummary:
The defendant Kayveon Barnett was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Reckless Homicide [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.02(1).
  • Adjudged Delinquent Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kayveon Barnett in court with attorney Richard L. Voss.  Defendant Kayveon Barnett in custody.  Sara B. Lewis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Prior to the case being called the victim/witness advocates inquired of the court if the victim's family may display in the courtroom a life-size banner of the victim, which the court allowed.
Defendant has a pending case 15CF2681, set before Branch 25/Branch 7 in August.
Sentencing proceeded.  Presentence Investigation reviewed.  Additions and corrections were made.  Statements by state, defense and defendant.   Additional statements by: Zakeya G.; Undraya B.; Yolander S.; Natasha B.; and Daniesha P.
As to count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 45 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 160 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 35 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 10 YEARS.
As to count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, consecutive to count 1.  CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS with the following conditions :
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges, DNA surcharges.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Defendant stipulated to restitution in the amount of $2000 payable to Crime Victim Compensation Fund.
-NO CONTACT with the victim's family.
-Participate in treatment is deemed appropriate.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  
Defendant is remanded and is to report to Dodge Correctional.

Defendant Kayveon Barnett in court with attorney Richard L. Voss.  Defendant Kayveon Barnett in custody.  Sara B. Lewis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Jurors returned at 8:45am and resumed deliberations.
At the hour of 10:10am the jury reached their verdicts.   Jury in the box at 10:30am and, by their foreperson (#22), brought in the following verdicts:
Count 1:  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of First Degree Reckless Homicide while armed with a dangerous weapon
Count 2:  We, the jury, find the defendant GUILTY of Felon in Possession of a Firearm. 
Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdicts received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdict and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdict.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction.  The court will order a PSI and remand defendant pending sentencing on 7-16-2015 at 8:15am.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
Witness fee request prepared for Dagheera C. will be forwarded to DAs Victim/Witness Services for approval and date confirmation.
